cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the optimization of parameterized hierarchical systems, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of nonlinear processing layers, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses speech front-end processing, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
